Excellent food, service, ambiance and location.
My husband and I took our two children there (age 6 and 3).
We chose to sit outside since we had the kids and would be less distracting to the other diners.
Our waitress was fantastic.
Seemed to have experience waiting on tables with children and didn't seem bothered by our kids countless demands.
My husband had deep fried fish, I had the perch.
Kids ate off the kids menu.
Cheese curds as an appetizer.
All fantastic.
Timely service, hot food, great coleslaw and tarter sauce!
I'm hooked.
I can't wait to go back and sit inside without our children.
I'm imagining that there are a lot of repeat customers that make The Klassik their "go to" restaurant.
We will definitely go back.

